metatags.name: Yahoo! Inc.
metatags.summary:
Updated: July 17, 2012

2012 Earnings: Second Quarter

In July 2012, the company reported that net income in the second quarter fell 4.2 percent from the same quarter a year earlier, to $228.5 million, or 18 cents a share. The company said revenue declined slightly to $1.22 billion.

The net income was above the expectation of Wall Street analysts. They had expected 20 cents a share and revenue of $1.1 billion, according to a survey of analysts provided by Capital IQ. Yahoo improved earnings largely because of cost-cutting. Using the accounting methods favored by the analysts, the company reported per-share net income of 27 cents a share.
